</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[806,1421,1850,1903]" lastBlockId="13.[164,779,1049,1407]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1048" pageId="12" pageNumber="1047">
<emphasis box="[806,925,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1047">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium to large sized species. Male body length ranges between 
<quantity box="[1181,1303,1881,1902]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="12" pageNumber="1047" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="14.0">14–21 mm</quantity>
; females, 14.5– 
<quantity box="[225,307,1049,1071]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
. Body colour dark brown to light brown marbled, rarely light testaceous. Male tenth tergite distal margin with wide, broadly rounded medial protrusion (
<figureCitation box="[264,363,1141,1163]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[164,243,1316,1335]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-192@15.[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. A–C, Troglophilus cavicola: A, male 18 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); B, female 18.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bukovik, Macedonia); C, male 18 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), lateral view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro). D–I ovipositor, lateral view: D, Troglophilus lazaropolensis, female 16.5 mm (Lazaropole, Macedonia); E, Troglophilus cavicola, female 18.5 mm (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); F, Troglophilus zorae sp. nov., paratype female 18 mm (Matka, Macedonia); G, Troglophilus brevicauda, female 15 mm (Olovo, Bosnia); H, Troglophilus ovuliformis, female 19.5 mm (D. Seoca, Montenegro); I, Troglophilus neglectus, female 15 mm (N. Breznica, Macedonia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442347/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
), separated by narrow more or less deep incision in two lobes. Female tenth abdominal tergite with slightly shallow excavated margin (
<figureCitation box="[172,271,1232,1255]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[164,243,1316,1335]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-192@15.[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. A–C, Troglophilus cavicola: A, male 18 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); B, female 18.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bukovik, Macedonia); C, male 18 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), lateral view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro). D–I ovipositor, lateral view: D, Troglophilus lazaropolensis, female 16.5 mm (Lazaropole, Macedonia); E, Troglophilus cavicola, female 18.5 mm (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); F, Troglophilus zorae sp. nov., paratype female 18 mm (Matka, Macedonia); G, Troglophilus brevicauda, female 15 mm (Olovo, Bosnia); H, Troglophilus ovuliformis, female 19.5 mm (D. Seoca, Montenegro); I, Troglophilus neglectus, female 15 mm (N. Breznica, Macedonia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442347/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
). Titillator is well sclerotized, long and slender, arched, and acute at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[667,767,1263,1285]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[164,243,1316,1335]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-192@15.[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. A–C, Troglophilus cavicola: A, male 18 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); B, female 18.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bukovik, Macedonia); C, male 18 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), lateral view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro). D–I ovipositor, lateral view: D, Troglophilus lazaropolensis, female 16.5 mm (Lazaropole, Macedonia); E, Troglophilus cavicola, female 18.5 mm (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); F, Troglophilus zorae sp. nov., paratype female 18 mm (Matka, Macedonia); G, Troglophilus brevicauda, female 15 mm (Olovo, Bosnia); H, Troglophilus ovuliformis, female 19.5 mm (D. Seoca, Montenegro); I, Troglophilus neglectus, female 15 mm (N. Breznica, Macedonia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442347/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor elongated and narrow, length ranges between 10.5–13.5 mm; the widest point is in its proximal third (
<figureCitation box="[369,467,1355,1377]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[164,243,1316,1335]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-192@15.[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. A–C, Troglophilus cavicola: A, male 18 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); B, female 18.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bukovik, Macedonia); C, male 18 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), lateral view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro). D–I ovipositor, lateral view: D, Troglophilus lazaropolensis, female 16.5 mm (Lazaropole, Macedonia); E, Troglophilus cavicola, female 18.5 mm (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); F, Troglophilus zorae sp. nov., paratype female 18 mm (Matka, Macedonia); G, Troglophilus brevicauda, female 15 mm (Olovo, Bosnia); H, Troglophilus ovuliformis, female 19.5 mm (D. Seoca, Montenegro); I, Troglophilus neglectus, female 15 mm (N. Breznica, Macedonia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442347/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
), ventral margin almost straight.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442343" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5442343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442343/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" startId="13.[164,243,948,967]" targetBox="[323,1283,196,919]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[164,1441,948,997]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,281,948,968]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Figure 10.</emphasis>
A–D, 
<taxonomicName box="[356,638,949,968]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azaropolensis">
<emphasis box="[356,638,949,968]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Troglophilus azaropolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lazaropole, Macedonia): A–B, male 15 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view; C, female 16.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view; D, male 15 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="13.[164,779,1449,1716]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">
<emphasis box="[164,309,1449,1470]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Distribution:</emphasis>
This species was originally described from the small cave Schelmenloch, south of Vienna, and it is of Dinaric origin. It is distributed from Lombardy and Vienna in the north-west, across Dinarids and Šar-Pindus mountain system, to central Greece in the south-east (Oiti Mt. after 
<bibRefCitation author="Willemse F" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" refId="ref11655" refString="Willemse F. 1984. Fauna Graeciae I. Catalogue of the Orthoptera of Greece. Athens: Hellenic Zoological Society." type="book" year="1984">Willemse, 1984</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[243,323,1633,1655]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="16.[144,223,1180,1199]" captionTargetBox="[144,1425,196,1151]" captionTargetId="figure-318@16.[144,1425,196,1151]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 13. The geographical distribution of Troglophilus cavicola (square – literature data). (ITA-Italy; A-Austria; SLO-Slovenia; CRO-Croatia; BIH-Bosnia and Herzegovina; SRB-Serbia; MNE-Montenegro; BUL-Bulgaria; ALB-Albania; MK-Macedonia; GRE-Greece)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442349" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442349/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). It is completely absent from southern and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[331,407,1664,1686]" name="Serbia" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[505,607,1664,1686]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
, and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[164,291,1694,1716]" name="Macedonia" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[164,779,1758,1902]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">
<emphasis box="[164,271,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Remarks:</emphasis>
Across its distribution range, the species is sympatric with all other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krauss" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Troglophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At some localities in western 
<collectingCountry box="[655,778,1820,1842]" name="Macedonia" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
it occurs sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": PAVICEVIC &amp; KARAMAN" authorityYear="2001" box="[529,719,1850,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lazaropolensis">
<emphasis box="[529,719,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">T. lazaropolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Karaman &amp; Hammouti &amp; Pavićević &amp; Kiefer &amp; Horvatović &amp; Seitz, 2011" authorityName="Karaman &amp; Hammouti &amp; Pavićević &amp; Kiefer &amp; Horvatović &amp; Seitz" authorityYear="2011" box="[164,252,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zorae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,252,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">T. zorae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[261,349,1881,1902]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[826,1441,1049,1132]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">
By examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1150,1247,1049,1071]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">holotype</typeStatus>
and specimens collected from the type locality, we concluded that 
<taxonomicName box="[826,952,1110,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukoviki">
<emphasis box="[826,952,1110,1132]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">T. bukoviki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": US" authorityYear="1970" box="[1234,1354,1110,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[1234,1354,1110,1132]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1048">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
